            "title": "Fulminant amoebic colitis following loperamide use.",
            "abstract": "Toxic megacolon is a rare consequence of infection with Entamoeba histolytica. We present such a patient in whom the course of disease may have been influenced by heavy loperamide use. Loperamide and other anti-motility agents have been implicated previously in the pathogenesis of toxic megacolon in patients with infectious gastroenteritis.",
